class Solution {
    public int minSteps(String s, String t) {
        int[] count = new int[26];
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            count[s.charAt(i) - 'a']++;
            count[t.charAt(i) - 'a']--;
        }
        int steps = 0;
        for (int i : count) {
            steps += Math.abs(i);
        }
        return steps / 2;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses a frequency count array to track character differences between the two strings, then calculates the minimum steps required to make them anagrams by summing the absolute differences and dividing by 2.
